---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | Alba Studio" description="About page for a UX designer portfolio.">
	<a class="skip-link" href="#main-content">Skip to content</a>

	<div class="page">
		<SiteHeader />

		<main id="main-content">
			<section class="hero">
				<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
				<h1 class="display-title">I design products that make complicated things feel clearer, calmer, and easier to use.</h1>
				<div class="hero-subgrid">
					<p class="hero-text">
						I'm Andrei Alba, a UX designer focused on turning dense workflows, fuzzy product
						requirements, and overloaded interfaces into experiences that people can actually
						navigate with confidence.
					</p>
					<p class="hero-note">
						My work tends to live where complexity matters: dashboards, internal tools, service
						platforms, and products where clarity directly affects trust.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="editorial-section">
				<div class="section-rail">
					<p class="section-kicker">Background</p>
				</div>
				<div class="story-block">
					<p>
						Over the last 10+ years, I've worked across SaaS, operations, service platforms,
						and internal tools where the design challenge is rarely just about making something
						look good. More often, it's about helping people understand what matters, what to
						do next, and why the product should feel trustworthy in the first place.
					</p>
					<p>
						I sit somewhere between product thinking, systems design, and interface craft. I
						care about hierarchy, pacing, micro-decisions, and the kind of details that make
						an experience feel intentional rather than merely complete.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="editorial-section">
				<div class="section-rail">
					<p class="section-kicker">How I Work</p>
				</div>
				<div class="story-block">
					<p>
						I work best in the messy middle: when the requirements are incomplete, the product
						has started to sprawl, and the team needs someone to create clarity without
						oversimplifying the problem.
					</p>
					<p>
						That usually means stepping back to understand the structure of the experience,
						deciding what deserves attention first, and then building a visual system strong
						enough to support that logic all the way through the final UI.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="editorial-section">
				<div class="section-rail">
					<p class="section-kicker">Focus</p>
				</div>
				<div class="story-block">
					<p>
						I'm especially interested in dashboards, workflow tools, AI-assisted interfaces,
						and products where reducing friction has a measurable impact on how confident people
						feel using the system.
					</p>
					<p>
						If something is too dense, too noisy, or too hard to follow, that's usually where I
						can do my best work.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.page {
		position: relative;
		width: min(calc(100% - 3rem), 78rem);
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 1.25rem 0 5rem;
	}

	.eyebrow,
	.section-kicker {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.hero {
		padding: 6rem 0 4rem;
	}

	.eyebrow,
	.section-kicker {
		margin: 0;
		color: var(--muted-foreground);
		font-style: italic;
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	.hero-subgrid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.3fr) minmax(0, 0.7fr);
		gap: 2rem;
		margin-top: 1.75rem;
	}

	.hero-text,
	.hero-note,
	.story-block p {
		font-size: 1.08rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.hero-note {
		color: var(--muted-foreground);
	}

	.editorial-section {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 16rem minmax(0, 1fr);
		gap: 2rem;
		padding: 2.5rem 0;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
	}

	.section-rail {
		align-self: start;
	}

	.story-block {
		display: grid;
		gap: 1rem;
		max-width: 52rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 980px) {
		.hero-subgrid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.page {
			width: min(calc(100% - 1.5rem), 78rem);
			padding-top: 1rem;
		}

		.hero {
			padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
		}

		.editorial-section {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.hero-text,
		.hero-note,
		.story-block p {
			font-size: 1.05rem;
		}
	}
</style>
